				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I'm trying it out now as i write this, in the 'tier2' area.  I'm a 59 mage and so far i've killed about a dozen goblins, and only one has been light blue (a shaman).  XP isn't all that great (my guess is maybe 1% per 5-6 kills) but the fights are CAKE against casters the pet basicly solos them, but melle are a pain in the ass.  Loot is nice, i've already gotten a diamond and about 5pp each kill.  I would recommend picking up a KEI before you come here, more kills = more xp = more cash to pay off the kei.  I wouldn't try canni-pet because of a high chance of mobs running into you.  Very nice spot once you get used it though.
<br />

<br />
Also, spy with eye of zomm around each corner, i've saved myself from one death so far.  Clay braclet (insta click eye of zomm) works wonders here.  The goblins seem to have a small assist range, however, so you can usally single with cancel magic.
<br />

<br />
My resists are as follows (with buffs)
<br />
83 PR
<br />
142 MR
<br />
73DR
<br />
138 FR
<br />
150 CR
<br />
I dont bother to DS myself because no goblin has even tried to fire nuke me yet.  It seems like the pet shares your resists, because so far shammies have tried to slow my pet about.. 8 times, and 0 have landed, even if they do land slow, you can heal it right off.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
